sentences: Susan Kay Quatro (born June 3, 1950) is an American singer-songwriter, musician, and actress.

sentences: Quatro moved to England in 1971, after being spotted by the record producer Mickie Most, who had by that time founded his own label, Rak Records.
She spent a year living in a hotel while being nurtured by Most, developing her skills and maturing.

This was the height of the glam rock period of the 1970s and Quatro, who wore leather clothes, portrayed a wild androgynous image while playing music that "hinged mostly on a hard rock chug beneath lyrics in which scansion overruled meaning.
"In 1972, Quatro embarked as a support act on a UK tour with Thin Lizzy and headliners Slade.

Rak Records arranged for her to use Thin Lizzy's newly acquired PA system during this, incurring a charge of £300 per week that enabled the Irish band to effectively purchase it at no cost to themselves.
